{"id": "EUVD-2025-205172", "enisaUuid": "c84c3a29-a0f9-32b5-ba3c-03fc1a39856c", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nping: Fix potentail NULL deref for /proc/net/icmp.\n\nAfter commit dbca1596bbb0 (\"ping: convert to RCU lookups, get rid\nof rwlock\"), we use RCU for ping sockets, but we should use spinlock\nfor /proc/net/icmp to avoid a potential NULL deref mentioned in\nthe previous patch.\n\nLet's go back to using spinlock there.\n\nNote we can convert ping sockets to use hlist instead of hlist_nulls\nbecause we do not use SLAB_TYPESAFE_BY_RCU for ping sockets.", "datePublished": "2025-12-24T12:30:26", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-24T12:30:26", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-53987", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/176cbb6da28f36506cc60a4bec4ab8df0c16713a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/5a08a32e624908890aa0a2eb442bb6a7669891a8", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ab5fb73ffa01072b4d8031cc05801fa1cb653bee"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-53987", "GHSA-m6qc-r2rx-cm2q"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "097bc7ae-857f-3acc-9d98-3a0473d03956", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "dbca1596bbb08318f5e3b3b99f8ca0a0d3830a65 <5a08a32e624908890aa0a2eb442bb6a7669891a8"}, {"id": "45d217c0-fec1-347b-88f7-574d7d80dfe2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "de3d723a3985f282a8c9e468d1e198616eb291c8"}, {"id": "47626517-dc24-33b1-a5f5-d037b79b9728", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2.11"}, {"id": "494ab8f3-2d74-3c3e-9572-6896c0ec67e4", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "dbca1596bbb08318f5e3b3b99f8ca0a0d3830a65 <ab5fb73ffa01072b4d8031cc05801fa1cb653bee"}, {"id": "56111c1b-ddbf-36eb-975f-936e58e88b5d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.1.24"}, {"id": "6abf5941-1930-3702-b440-86100fbad143", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.3"}, {"id": "b6403f14-0176-32ea-9102-